{"id":2507,"date":"2021-03-02T11:06:58","date_gmt":"2021-03-02T09:06:58","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/154.0.202.153\/?page_id=2507"},"modified":"2024-04-27T11:32:20","modified_gmt":"2024-04-27T09:32:20","slug":"standing-committee-on-standing-rules-orders-internal-arrangements","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/standing-committee-on-standing-rules-orders-internal-arrangements\/","title":{"rendered":"Standing Committee on Standing Rules, Orders &#038; Internal Arrangements"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_accordion][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Mandate&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675935370-0134560d-4d1d&#8221;][vc_column_text]The Committee has the duty to assist and act on matters referred to it by the House for scrutiny and to submit reports on:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>The accounts showing the appropriation of the sums granted by Parliament to meet public expenditure of the Republic;<\/li>\n<li>Such other accounts and any other matter or task as my be referred to the Committee by the House or under any other law;<\/li>\n<li>All reports of the Auditor General on any such accounts;<\/li>\n<li>All accounts and reports of accounts where the State has interests; and<\/li>\n<li>All State-Owned Enterprises and Parastatals.<\/li>\n<li>The Committee reports on its findings and makes its recommendations to the Assembly for consideration and debate.<\/li>\n<li>Upon adoption of the reports and recommendations by the Assembly, the Committee has a duty to report on the implementation of the recommendations as adopted.<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;O\/M\/A Served&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675935394-b261dfb1-f78e&#8221;][vc_column_text]<\/p>\n<table width=\"600px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\"list\">Parliament of Namibia<\/div>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<p>[\/vc_column_text][\/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=&#8221;Clerks&#8221; tab_id=&#8221;1614675960778-8bd7